      <abstract>
        <p>Sam Van Fleet letter on Mimi Sheraton's April 1 travel article on cook's tour of Milan</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: With regard to Mimi Sheraton's ''Cook's Tour of Milan'' (April 1): If only I had known sooner about the culinary delights of that city.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: With regard to Mimi Sheraton's ''Cook's Tour of Milan'' (April 1): If only I had known sooner about the culinary delights of that city.</p>
        <p>During a recent trip to Italy, my wife and I booked extended stays in several cities that were obvious choices for first-timers -- Rome, Florence, Siena and so on -- leaving only a two-day layover in Milan before returning home.</p>
        <p>What a mistake that turned out to be. We had the good fortune to pick a hotel next door to the fabulous Peck food store. Oh, the wonders of that place. And the marvelous bakery just a few doors down, followed by the superb restaurant in a courtyard near the Duomo, only to be topped by the sublime Antica Osteria del Ponte on the outskirts of town. So much food and so little time!</p>
        <p>Thanks to that experience and to Ms. Sheraton's article, we will be sure during our next visit to schedule plenty of time to enjoy the underrated city of Milan.</p>
        <p>Sam Van Fleet  Vashon Island, Wash.</p>
      </block>
